The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Mumbai, June 30: The Reserve Bank wants banks to prepare a risk management system for their exposure to the real estate sector. It wants banks to fix exposure limits. There should be a board-mandated policy in respect of real estate exposure, which may include exposure limits, collaterals, margins, sanctioning authority and the sector to be financed. However, the actual limits and margins may vary depending upon the bank?s portfolio size, risk appetite and risk containing abilities, the RBI said today.

 New Delhi, June 30: The stringent prevention of money laundering act, which will come into force from tomorrow, has made it mandatory for banks, FIs and financial intermediaries to report all suspicious transactions and cash transaction over Rs 10 lakh.

 Mumbai, June 30: Indian Oil Corp today raised prices of aviation turbine fuel by about 6 per cent with effect from midnight tonight. 

 New Delhi, June 30: The Centre?s income tax collections have dropped 29 per cent to Rs 7,091 crore during April-June 23. However, corporate tax rose 166 per cent at Rs 9,079 crore.

 Calcutta, June 30: A group of shareholders today filed an application in the high court challenging the order of the Company Law Board in connection with injunction on transfer of shares of MP Birla group firm East India Investment Corporation.




